      "term": "semidurables",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "goods designed to last a moderately long time but are not permanent, often used for short to medium-term use or temporary purposes",
          "examples": ["The shop sells semidurables like kitchenware and containers intended to wear out after a few seasons."],
